==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|la}} noun {{term|sacramentum}}, from the verb {{term|sacrare||hallow, consecrate}}, from adjective {{term|sacer||sacred}}, + suffix {{term|-mentum}}.

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{Christianity}} A sacred act or ceremony in [[Christianity]].  In Roman Catholic theology, a '''sacrament''' is defined as "an outward sign instituted by Christ to give grace."

